Ent√£o eu estava empolgado em ir ver a banda de tributo aos Bee Gees dos EUA no √∫ltimo domingo. O tempo estava perfeito, nossos assentos estavam perfeitos e o show come√ßou bem na hora. Mas foi a√≠ que a perfei√ß√£o terminou. Por que uma banda de tributo precisa de um abridor? Enquanto a banda tributo da Am√©rica foi excelente, eles tocaram por meia hora, e ent√£o uns bons 15 MINUTOS DEPOIS, os Bee Gees dos EUA sa√≠ram. Eles tocaram uma boa m√∫sica de dan√ßa por 30 MINUTOS antes de fazerem uma pausa! Ningu√©m podia acreditar! E ent√£o eles se foram por mais 30 MINUTOS! A multid√£o estava ficando MUITO inquieta, pelo menos na parte de tr√°s onde est√°vamos. Depois de alguns gritos e vaias barulhentos, eles finalmente voltaram e tocaram por mais 45 minutos. Mas eles cometeram um grande erro. Com um local como esse, voc√™ quer dan√ßar ao som de uma boa m√∫sica disco, pela qual os Bee Gees s√£o famosos. Em vez disso, essa banda literalmente tocou quatro ou cinco baladas lentas IN A ROW, a ponto de as pessoas come√ßarem a fazer as malas e ir embora. Talvez eles tivessem circunst√¢ncias atenuantes, mas uma banda de abertura? Uma pausa de 30 minutos? Um monte de m√∫sicas lentas? N√£o. Tomem uma li√ß√£o, rapazes, de algumas das outras bandas de tributo que v√™m ou perdem seu p√∫blico. Voc√™ me perdeu.  (Original) I usually love going to the bandshell. The venue, the setting, the food, the music is usually pretty great. So I was excited about going to see the U.S. Bee Gees tribute band last Sunday. The weather was perfect, our seats were perfect, and the show started right on time. But that's where the perfection ended. Why does a tribute band need an opener? While the America tribute band was excellent, they played for a half hour, and then a good 15 MINUTES LATER, the U.S. Bee Gees came out. They played some great dance music for 30 MINUTES before they took a break! No one could believe it! And then they were gone for another 30 MINUTES! The crowd was getting VERY restless, at least in the back where we were. After some noisy caterwauling and booing, they finally came back out and played for another 45 minutes. But they made a huge mistake. With a venue like that, you want to be up and dancing to some great disco music, which the Bee Gees are famous for. Instead, this band literally played four or five slow ballads IN A ROW, to the point where people began packing up and leaving. Why would you play slow ballads when everyone just wants to dance the night away!? Very poor decision. Would I go to see them again? No way. Maybe they had extenuating circumstances, but an opening band? A 30-minute BREAK? A bunch of slow songs? Nope. Take a lesson, guys, from some of the other tribute bands that come or lose your audience. You lost me.
